               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-213-person1667">
                  JAMES 
                  MUNTING
               <interp inst="t18311201-213-person1667" type="surname" value="MUNTING"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-213-person1667" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-213-person1667" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I keep a book-shop in the New-cut. On the 27th of October the prisoner came to sell two books for 2s. 6d.; I asked if they belonged to him - he said Yes, and that he lived at Kennington; I offered him 1s. 6d., and sent Nathan with him, to see if he lived there.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-213-person1668">
                  NATHAN 
                  NATHAN
               <interp inst="t18311201-213-person1668" type="surname" value="NATHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-213-person1668" type="given" value="NATHAN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18311201-213-person1668" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I went with the prisoner, and when we got three quarters of a mile, I asked if he lived at Queen's-row, Kennington; he said he had lived there three months ago - he at last ran away; I overtook him and gave him in custody.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18311201-213-person1669">
                  ALICE 
                  STACEY
               <interp inst="t18311201-213-person1669" type="surname" value="STACEY"></interp>
